725224f-b.title: Queens: 33rd Avenue - Parsons Boulevard
725224f-b.text:
Thirty-third Ave. (Mitchell Ave.), north side, east of Parsons
Boulevard about 170 feet, showing the home of Mrs. Warder Poor erected
by her in 1920. However, a caretaker of Walter Bownes place states that
W. Mitchell built this house on the site of a barn when he sold the
Hamilton Homestead. This is a set of two views.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
